      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the pastry",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Rub the pastry-quantity cold {{unsalted-butter}} into {{plain-flour}} and the pastry {{caster-sugar}} until the mixture resembles breadcrumbs. Add the {{egg-yolks}} and 2 tablespoons of cold water; mix to a firm dough. Wrap and refrigerate for 30 minutes. Roll out and line a 23 cm loose-bottomed tart tin. Refrigerate for 30 minutes.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the filling and bake",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 180°C fan (200°C conventional). Beat the filling-quantity softened {{unsalted-butter}} with the filling {{caster-sugar}} until combined. Beat in {{eggs}} one at a time. Stir in {{cream-cheese}}, {{currants}}, {{nutmeg-whole}}, and the zest from {{lemon}}. Pour the filling into the uncooked pastry case. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes until the filling is set and lightly coloured on top, and the pastry is golden. The centre should have a very slight wobble. Cool in the tin for 30 minutes before slicing.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Notes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "The pastry base will be softer than a blind-baked case; this is correct for the traditional version. For a crisper base, blind bake for 10 minutes before adding the filling.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Freshly grated nutmeg is markedly more fragrant than pre-ground. The quantity here is generous; reduce to half a teaspoon if you prefer a more subtle spice.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "The tart is traditionally eaten at room temperature, not cold from the fridge.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
